  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provide Care for Afghanistan&apos;s Abandoned Children</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">We have been working in Afghanistan since the US Air Force loaned us a few helicopters to do our work in 2010. Early supply missions helped us locate and test Janagha Jaheed (JJ), our local partner in Baharak, Badakshan. Eventually we worked with JJ to lay down our first Children&apos;s Garden and chicken egg farm. Local children, including 20 children who lost their fathers to war, spend time in our garden (we have a master gardener who does the planning and hard work) and take home vegetables/eggs.</narrative>
  </description>
